The paper deals with image-to-image translation, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed framework involves the use of a GAN, which is a popular deep learning technique (cs.LG). The framework also involves the use of semantic segmentation, which is a common technique in computer vision for identifying objects in an image based on their semantic meaning (cs.AI). The paper also involves the evaluation of the proposed framework on several image-to-image translation tasks, which falls under the category of graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM).
